WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.790 --> 00:00:03.970
&gt;&gt; From the Library of
Congress in Washington D.C.

00:00:19.060 --> 00:00:20.360
&gt;&gt; Mary-Jane Deeb: Well,
good afternoon, everyone,

00:00:20.360 --> 00:00:23.230
and welcome to the African
and Middle East Division.

00:00:23.230 --> 00:00:26.830
I'm Mary-Jane Deeb Chief of the
division, and I'm really very,

00:00:26.830 --> 00:00:32.080
very happy to see you all here
for this special presentation

00:00:32.080 --> 00:00:37.660 position:56%
with Israeli artist Avner Moriah who
will talk to us about his new book

00:00:37.660 --> 00:00:42.550
"From Text to Image:
Illumination as Visual Commentary".

00:00:42.550 --> 00:00:44.650
I hope it will not be
only about the new book,

00:00:44.650 --> 00:00:47.740
that it'll be about more than that.

00:00:47.740 --> 00:00:50.350
As most of you already
know, our division,

00:00:50.350 --> 00:00:54.150 position:56%
and this is my little commercial for
our division because we're webcast,

00:00:54.150 --> 00:00:59.280
and we want the world to know
where this event is taking place.

00:00:59.280 --> 00:01:03.870
So, our division is made
up of three sections.

00:01:03.870 --> 00:01:07.250
The Hebraic section, of
course, the African section,

00:01:07.250 --> 00:01:09.060
and the Near East section.

00:01:09.060 --> 00:01:13.780
We're responsible for materials
from 78 countries around the world,

00:01:13.780 --> 00:01:17.470
from the near east,
central Asia, the Caucasus,

00:01:17.470 --> 00:01:20.000
as well as from the
entire continent of Africa.

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.220
And, of course, for Hebraic, we
collect from around the world.

00:01:24.220 --> 00:01:27.930
We're very active in acquiring
and developing our collections,

00:01:27.930 --> 00:01:32.640
greeting visitors coming from
countries from our regions,

00:01:32.640 --> 00:01:37.550
and organizing programs,
symposia, workshops.

00:01:37.550 --> 00:01:46.220 position:56%
We're also have exhibits and special
displays, and we had a big one,

00:01:46.220 --> 00:01:53.950
a big exhibit on the Hebrew
book a few years ago which was,

00:01:53.950 --> 00:01:59.940
which brought in hundreds of
thousands of people to see some

00:01:59.940 --> 00:02:05.150
of the treasures that we hold here.

00:02:05.150 --> 00:02:12.620
We are particularly happy to have
Avner Moriah here with us today.

00:02:12.620 --> 00:02:17.490
Not only because we
like to invite scholars

00:02:17.490 --> 00:02:23.910
to discuss their productions,
their creations, their books

00:02:23.910 --> 00:02:28.950
and how they use the materials in
the collections, in our collection,

00:02:28.950 --> 00:02:34.410
other collections, to write their
works or to produce their books,

00:02:34.410 --> 00:02:40.880
but we are happy because
Avner Moriah's works,

00:02:40.880 --> 00:02:44.370
his illustrations,
focus on the Bible.

00:02:44.370 --> 00:02:48.580
And, the Hebraic section's holdings
are especially strong in the areas

00:02:48.580 --> 00:02:52.330
of the Bibles, or the
Bible and rabbinic liturgy

00:02:52.330 --> 00:02:55.000
and Hebrew language and literature.

00:02:55.000 --> 00:03:00.590
The section is also expanding its
collection of modern artist books

00:03:00.590 --> 00:03:04.850
on the Bible, and so it is fitting
to have Avner Moriah come and talk

00:03:04.850 --> 00:03:08.560
to us about his journey through
the Bible, and how he became

00:03:08.560 --> 00:03:11.280
such an illustrious artist.

00:03:11.280 --> 00:03:14.610
We hold his beautifully
illustrated book of Genesis

00:03:14.610 --> 00:03:17.030
and have just acquired
his most recent.

00:03:17.030 --> 00:03:18.860
&gt;&gt; Don't give it away.

00:03:18.860 --> 00:03:20.580
&gt;&gt; Okay. I won't.

00:03:20.580 --> 00:03:21.880
I'm stopping here.

00:03:21.880 --> 00:03:25.180
I've been stopped,
so I do not continue.

00:03:25.180 --> 00:03:27.900
Okay. So, we will surprise you.

00:03:27.900 --> 00:03:29.200
I think, put it this way.

00:03:29.200 --> 00:03:36.820
We will surprise you, okay,
with a display of his books,

00:03:36.820 --> 00:03:41.170
of his illustrated books and
also of some of our treasures,

00:03:41.170 --> 00:03:47.000
some of our older Bibles, some of
the unique Bibles that we hold.

00:03:47.000 --> 00:03:50.860
So, that will be a surprise
at the end of the program.

00:03:50.860 --> 00:03:57.040
And now, Dr. Ann Brener, the Hebrew
specialist in the Hebraic section,

00:03:57.040 --> 00:04:00.510
will introduce our
speaker for today.

00:04:00.510 --> 00:04:06.060
[ Inaudible Conversation
and Laughter ]

00:04:06.060 --> 00:04:07.360
&gt;&gt; Ann Brener: I'm sorry.

00:04:07.360 --> 00:04:08.660
That just kind of popped out.

00:04:08.660 --> 00:04:12.050
It is a surprise.

00:04:12.050 --> 00:04:14.970
[laughs] The Bible has been a
constant focus of creativity

00:04:14.970 --> 00:04:19.800 position:56%
through the ages, inviting scholars,
poets, artists, and dreamers to fill

00:04:19.800 --> 00:04:24.460
in the gaps, flesh out the details,
and delve into the meanings.

00:04:24.460 --> 00:04:27.260
Today's speaker is
one of those artists,

00:04:27.260 --> 00:04:32.700 position:56%
and today's display a tribute to his
unique vision of a biblical text.

00:04:32.700 --> 00:04:34.810
Avner Moriah is one
of the best known

00:04:34.810 --> 00:04:37.200
and widely collected
artists in Israel today.

00:04:37.200 --> 00:04:40.320
He is what we call in
Hebrew a [Hebrew language].

00:04:40.320 --> 00:04:42.720
He's a national treasure.

00:04:42.720 --> 00:04:46.140
He is a Jerusalem artist
who was born in Jerusalem.

00:04:46.140 --> 00:04:50.640 position:56%
He lives and works in Jerusalem, but
his works have reached every corner

00:04:50.640 --> 00:04:53.860
of the globe and they grace
the finest of collections,

00:04:53.860 --> 00:04:58.450
the Metropolitan Museum of Art,
the Israel Museum in Jerusalem,

00:04:58.450 --> 00:05:01.860
the Art Institute of
Boston, and many, many more.

00:05:01.860 --> 00:05:05.830
Here in the Library of
Congress, we also collect him,

00:05:05.830 --> 00:05:10.870
and indeed his illuminated book
of Genesis as Dr. Deeb just said,

00:05:10.870 --> 00:05:13.690
it has long been one of our
favorite showpieces here

00:05:13.690 --> 00:05:16.280
in the Hebraic section.

00:05:16.280 --> 00:05:18.910
We have a special surprise
for you today.

00:05:18.910 --> 00:05:20.360
Now, I'll say it.

00:05:20.360 --> 00:05:24.630
As you know, there will be a
display following today's talk,

00:05:24.630 --> 00:05:28.920
and you will be able to see
some really gorgeous examples

00:05:28.920 --> 00:05:32.940
of Avner's work together
with some rare editions

00:05:32.940 --> 00:05:35.450
of the biblical texts
that have inspired him.

00:05:35.450 --> 00:05:38.310
But, what you don't know
because we didn't know

00:05:38.310 --> 00:05:42.390
until yesterday ourselves, was
that we're also going to be able

00:05:42.390 --> 00:05:46.090
to display, I think for the first
time in America, his new book,

00:05:46.090 --> 00:05:50.320
his next book in his biblical
journey, the book of Exodus.

00:05:50.320 --> 00:05:54.530
It is absolutely gorgeous, and
it's on display for you afterwards.

00:05:54.530 --> 00:05:57.870
So, we're so delighted
that worked out.

00:05:57.870 --> 00:06:02.770
It was due to the generosity
of the Coven Family Endowment

00:06:02.770 --> 00:06:05.850
that we were able to make
this really extravagantly

00:06:05.850 --> 00:06:08.050
beautiful purchase.

00:06:08.050 --> 00:06:12.560
And, I'm delighted to have
the opportunity to thank them.

00:06:12.560 --> 00:06:14.820
I also want to thank the Ms. Golina
Teverovski [assumed spelling]

00:06:14.820 --> 00:06:18.060
in Acquisitions Division who
worked some kind of magic

00:06:18.060 --> 00:06:21.980
in getting this book straight from
the binding and into the shelves

00:06:21.980 --> 00:06:23.710
of the Library of Congress
in record time,

00:06:23.710 --> 00:06:26.310
just in time for today's display.

00:06:26.310 --> 00:06:27.610
So, thanks to Golina.

00:06:27.610 --> 00:06:28.970
Are you here, Golina?

00:06:28.970 --> 00:06:33.540
No? Well, she deserves our thanks.

00:06:33.540 --> 00:06:37.900 position:56%
All great stories seem to begin with
a quest, and today we are privileged

00:06:37.900 --> 00:06:41.860
to welcome Avner Moriah into our
reading room and hear firsthand

00:06:41.860 --> 00:06:44.670
about his own journey
through the Bible.

00:06:44.670 --> 00:06:48.510
So, please join me in
welcoming Avner Moriah.

00:06:48.510 --> 00:06:57.120
[ Applause ]

